      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA131-kiḷavi">itu maṇamaṉaiyiṉ piṟṟaiñāṉṟu pukka tōḻiyait talaivaṉ “vēṟupaṭāmai yāṟṟuvittāy periyai kāṇ” eṉṟāṟkut tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said to HIM who said to the confidante, who had afterwards entered the marriage house: “look at you great one who gave strength so that [SHE] would not ungo changes”.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA131">
<l>            āṭiya toḻilu malkiya poḻilu</l>
<l>            muḷḷa lākā vuyavu neñcamō</l>
<l>            ṭūṭalu muṭaiyamō vuyarmaṇaṟ cērppa</l>
<l>            tiraimuti raraiya taṭantāṭ ṭāḻaic</l>
<l>            cuṟavumarup paṉṉa muṭṭō ṭociya </l>
<l>            viṟavā riṉakkuru kiṟaikoḷa virukku</l>
<l>            naṟavumaki ḻirukkai naṟṟērp periyaṉ</l>
<l>            kaṭkamaḻ poṟaiyā ṟaṉṉave</l>
<l>            ṉaṟṟō ṇekiḻa maṟatta ṉumakkē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Are we, o man from the coast of high sands, to have vexation,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with a suffering heart, not to remember<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uḷḷal ākā</term> has to be read here as a second verbal noun depending on <term xml:lang="ta">uṭaiyam</term>, standing in apposition to <term xml:lang="ta">ūṭal</term>, negated, however, by <term xml:lang="ta">ākā</term>.</note></l>
<l>the games<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">oḻil</term>, chosen for the sake of rhyming with <term xml:lang="ta">poḻil</term>, presumably refers here to the things THEY did together, which does not quite agree with the usual meaning "task", though something like "occupation" might do.</note> we played and the grove where we stayed?</l>
<l rend="indent">– in order to forget you,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">maṟattal numakku</term> is glossed by T.V.G. as <term xml:lang="ta">nīr maṟattaṟku</term>, and, indeed, how else to take it?</note> while my good shoulders get emaciated,</l>
<l rend="indent3">like the river with [its] burden smelling of nectar</l>
<l rend="indent">of Periyaṉ with good chariot from a seat where they delight in toddy,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the heron, from a group feeding on prawn,</l>
<l rend="indent3">in order to take a seat perches,</l>
<l rend="indent2">for the palm leaf, thorny like a swordfish’s saw(?), to be broken,</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the broad-based Tāḻai tree with a trunk saturated(?)</l>
<l rend="indent4">by the waves<note place="foot">T.V.G. explains <term xml:lang="ta">tirai</term> here to mean the folds in the trunk of an aged tree.</note>.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
